subSection.paragraph:
The mutant forms LeAOS3 F 108 L , ZmAOS1 F 95 L , and PpAOS2 F 93 L possessed the altered product specificities and converted the substrates, (9(
S
)- HPOD , 9(
S
)- HPOT , 13(
S
)- HPOD , and 13(
S
)- HPOT ), into the epoxyalcohols (the EAS products) along with α- ketols ( Figs. 3–5 and Supplementary Figs. S1–S 2 ). For instance, the LeAOS3 F 108 L mutant form exhibited the dual AOS / EAS activity possessing mainly AOS activity (87.3%) towards preferred substrate – 9(
S
)- HPOD and mainly EAS activity (77.5%) towards non-preferred substrate – 13(
S
)- HPOD . Furthermore, some mutant forms possessed also the HPL activity. The ZmAOS1 F 95 L mutant form possessed mainly the AOS or HPL activities being incubated with 9(
S
)- HPOD /T (53.8% and 59.4%, respectively) or 13(
S
)- HPOD /T (47.0% and 58.6%, respectively). The EAS activity of this mutant form was minor towards all examined hydroperoxides. The PpAOS2 F 93 L mutant form possessed almost only EAS activity towards 9-hydroperoxides, while as HPL (43.2%) or AOS (58.6%) activities towards 13(
S
)- HPOD and 13(
S
)- HPOT , respectively. In contrast to other studied enzymes, the LuAOS F 155 L mutant form kept the unaltered AOS activity.

The recombinant WT enzymes and their mutant forms (10 μg) were incubated with 100 μg of 9(
S
)- HPOD , 9(
S
)- HPOT , 13(
S
)- HPOD , or 13(
S
)- HPOT in Na-phosphate buffer (100 mM, 10 ml), pH 7.0, 23 ̊ C , for 15 min. The reaction mixtures were acidified to pH 6.0, and the products were extracted with hexane/ethyl acetate (1:1, v/v) mixture, then methylated with ethereal diazomethane and trimethylsilylated with pyridine/hexamethyldisilazane/trimethylchlorosilane (1:1:1, v/v) mixture at 23 ̊ C for 30 min. The silylation reagents were evaporated in vacuo. The dry residue was dissolved in 100 μl of hexane and subjected to GC-MS analyses. When specified, the products were reduced with NaBH 4 , then methylated and trimethylsilylated. Alternatively, the products of NaBH 4 reduction were hydrogenated over PtO 2 , then methylated and trimethylsilylated. Products (without or with the preliminary NaBH 4 reduction) were analysed as Me esters/ TMS derivatives (Me/ TMS ) by GC-MS as described before ( Grechkin et al., 2006 ).

